Inland Municipality Streamlines Rules to Draw Investment 
Chongqing Municipality in southwest China abolished 44 licenses and
approval requirements and 76 items of compulsory payments of companies
so as to encourage businesses and individuals to invest in this
southwest China industrial heartland.
Chongqing Mayor Bao Xuding said here today that the municipal
government will abolish all local regulations that run contradictory to
the central government's policy to accelerate the development of
western China.
The city has also cut links between 207 intermediate agents and their
former government sponsors. These agents include accounting, auditing
and taxation offices.
